44
00:02:26.090 --> 00:02:30.130
So, we have assets, which are resources
owned by the business that are expected to

45
00:02:30.130 --> 00:02:32.350
provide future economic benefits.

46
00:02:32.350 --> 00:02:37.420
By that we mean they'll either provide
cash coming in in the future, or

47
00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:40.360
they'll save the company from
having to spend cash in the future.

48
00:02:41.660 --> 00:02:45.970
Liabilities are claims on assets by
creditors who are non-owners that

49
00:02:45.970 --> 00:02:50.219
represents some obligation to make future
payment of cash, goods, or services.

50
00:02:51.430 --> 00:02:55.980
And stockholders equity is the claim on
the assets by the owners of the business.

51
00:02:55.980 --> 00:02:59.006
So, we have the balance sheet equation
that assets equal liabilities plus

52
00:02:59.006 --> 00:03:02.160
stockholders equity,
which means that your resources,

53
00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:07.160
assets, equal claims on those
resources by outsiders, creditors.

54
00:03:07.160 --> 00:03:09.720
And then, claims by the owners,
stockholders equity.

55
00:03:09.720 --> 00:03:13.720
Stockholders equity is made
up of a couple components.

56
00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:16.420
First of all, there's contributed capital.

57
00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:19.100
This is the common stock, or
additional paying capital,

58
00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.770
that arises when the company
sells shares of stock.

59
00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:26.659
And retained earnings, which arise when
the company operates the business.

60
00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:30.910
Retained earnings are increased by
revenues, which is what you get

61
00:03:30.910 --> 00:03:34.690
when the company delivers goods or
services to its customers.

62
00:03:34.690 --> 00:03:39.480
They're decreased by expenses, which are
the costs of generating those revenues.

63
00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:41.679
Also, decreased by dividends,

64
00:03:41.679 --> 00:03:46.245
which are decisions to pay out either
cash or stock to shareholders.

